  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (d1c84e3 2023-03-13T00:07:48.790822528Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge \r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen using `forge script --broadcast --slow -vvvv` without the `--legacy` flag on mainnet, the baseFee seems wrong(excessive).\r\n\r\nOn this repo for [example](https://github.com/bgd-labs/static-a-token-v3/blob/main/Makefile) the gas estimation yields:\r\n\r\n**mainnet --legacy**: 36gwei\r\n**mainnet**: 73gwei \r\n**etherscan reference**: 35-38 gwei\r\n\r\n**polygon --legacy**: 140 gwei\r\n**polygon**: 177 gwei \r\n**polygonscan reference**: 130-180 gwei\r\n\r\nProbably there was some timing issue when producing the numbers.\r\nThat said for me eth non-legacy transactions are consistently priced with a 100% premium, where on other networks they seem to be on par.\r\n\r\nAdditional info:\r\nI tried a few different rpcs for mainnet (alchemy & public ones) and seems like it's always the same behavior. 1559 on ethereum being excessively priced.",
