    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "this appears to be a direct result of https://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs/blob/2cead3e11160a48b403d1334eab329d38f10b4fa/ethers-core/src/utils/mod.rs#L615-L625\r\n\r\nwhich simply doubles the base fee (leading to the 36->73 relationship)\r\n\r\nAn excessive base fee in a tx is only a problem if the sending account doesn't have funds to cover the max. The basefee here is the max, not the effective payment. As long as the max priority fee is low (seems like it's 1 gwei?) there shouldn't be an issue. This will not cause users to overpay, it will cause their transactions to confirm even if there's a price surge\r\n",
