    "body": "@prestwich interesting\r\nWhat is the rationale behind this surge multiplier (being different for different base_fee levels)?\r\nThe lower the base fee, the higher the multiplier? \r\nTo me this assumption seems to be incorrect/unfounded as\r\n- on ethereum the price is \"mostly stable\" (yes it moves up and down, but usually not more than a few gwei per block)\r\n- where on polygon which i assume has a higher base fee already, the volatility is quite high from block to block\r\n\r\nWhile i see now, that eventually it doesn't matter (if you have enough funds on your wallet, i assume otherwise you cannot even execute?).\r\nI think it would be good if estimation would be somewhat closer to reality. At least for me when trying non legacy, the estimated 2x was concerning so i used legacy - assume others might experience the same.\r\n",
